    "content": "Lea, the original 10 are signed off. Done. No more discussion on those.\n\n**One separate change remains.** This is NOT one of the original 10. It came from Heydon's contrast audit after those were committed:\n\n`--color-fg-muted` needs to change from `var(--color-gray-500)` to `var(--color-gray-600)`.\n\nLine 212 in the current file. One line. I've approved this as a design token governance change. Can you confirm whether you've seen this request and whether you'll make it? If you've already done it and I missed the commit, let me know.\n\nAlso noted on the auth form CSS -- agreed, Task #5 is the right time. The class names in my spec (`.auth-form`, `.auth-form__fields`, etc.) may end up different in the actual template. I'm flexible on names -- the spacing values and layout structure are what matter. We'll align when the time comes.\n\nThe `:has([aria-invalid=\"true\"])` pattern sounds good. Looking forward to seeing it."
  }
